 Information Security Sr. Manager/Global Information Security Cyber Intelligence Lead
 
 Description: 
Cigna Information Protection team is seeking a Global Information Protection Cyber Intelligence Lead who is very motivated and able to take on the challenge of building and maturing a comprehensive security metrics program. The ideal candidate has a deep understanding of metrics-driven reporting practices and is able to articulate a clear story to a wide range of audiences using complex data and information. They will also have the unique benefit of having overview and insight into the whole spectrum of our cyber security activity at Cigna.
 
The Information Protection Cyber Intelligence Leader will drive the effort to build a comprehensive and sustainable cyber security metrics and reporting program. They will do this through identification and standardization of key cyber metrics, dashboards that provide visibility, insights, and accountability, identify gaps and trends in our cyber security controls, and inform our strategy and operations with audiences ranging from daily operational teams to the Board of Directors.
 
 Responsibilities: 
Define, manage, and implement plans to develop and mature a comprehensive, end-to-end cyber security metrics program
 Lead a small team of analysts (direct reports and matrix partners) and executive steering committee to develop and apply fast pace, scalable analytical/reporting solutions for CIP and matrix partners within the Cyber Security space
 Provide individual and team leadership to the Cyber Security Intelligence team as they develop capabilities and achieve their career goals
 Maintain governance and program charter, define key roles and responsibilities and identify resources and skills for additional technology hires
 Interpret risk measures into established quantifiable risk models for measurement across various functions and groups
 Lead discussions to identify risk tolerance and thresholds for various security domains aligned to NIST 800:53
 Identify and establish key performance, risk, and control indicators and metrics that will drive impactful actions and decisions to address key risks and threats, improve operational performance, and drive capability maturity
 Develop high quality metrics reporting and dashboards for key audiences ranging from operational teams to our Board of Directors
 Lead implementation of tools and solutions to automate and visualize metrics, reporting, and dashboards for key audiences
 Apply advanced analytics models and artificial intelligence, where appropriate, to derive additional insight from key metrics
 Drive the adoption and use of key metrics and reporting across the cyber security organization to inform daily operations, tactical activities, strategic planning, and risk management
 Communicate metrics and insights across various levels of the organization; conduct executive level presentations and briefings discussing trends, anomalies, and necessary actions
 Partner with cyber security, IT, and Cigna leaders and stakeholders to continuously refresh and define new and relevant metrics and reporting needs
 Ensure consistency and accuracy of metrics and reporting
 
 Qualifications: 
A Bachelor's degree in computer science, information systems, information protection/security or related Technology field is preferred
 7+ years in cyber security and or related security assurance and risk related experience
 Strong understanding of end-to-end cyber security metrics process including metrics collection, tracking, and reporting, including ownership and responsibilities for each activity
 Strategic communicator - able to simplify the complex with proven experience presenting to top level executives; excellent written and verbal communication skills
 Demonstrated collaborative leadership in implementing innovative analytic and management solutions that drive results
 Strong attention to detail
 Broad cyber security industry, technology, and security knowledge including understanding of operations, technology, communications and processes
 Consulting skills - able to assimilate business knowledge and knowledge of internal customer's unique needs/situation. Provide options and tools to make informed decisions
 Outstanding interpersonal skills with the proven ability to influence and achieve alignment across a range of different opinions and interests
 Ability to work independently and make objective decisions independently
 
 Desired Qualifications: 
Masterâ€™s Degree or equivalent experience preferred
 3-5 years of extensive experience designing and delivering cyber security metrics, reports, and dashboards that provide actionable insights for diverse audiences including senior management and Board of Directors
 Prior experience and knowledge of reporting, visualization, and analytics solutions such as MS PowerBI, Tableau, Splunk, AWS, native Microsoft Azure and/or GCP analytics services, etc.
 Industry certification (e.g., CISSP, CISM, CCSP, etc.)
 Experience with Agile and Waterfall solution development approaches
 Understanding and working knowledge of quantitative risk analysis such as FAIR
 
This position is not eligible to be performed in Colorado.
 
